<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUN RIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding your editorial, "Nuts over Guns," June 23: 
</P>
<P>
 You asked, "When will America get the message?" What message are you referring 
to? The message that no one can be held responsible for his or her actions, 
that there is always someone or something else (a gun) to blame? It is a fact 
that drunken drivers kill people. Usually, the alcohol is blamed.But we don't 
blame the instrument, the auto. When O.J. Simpson's ex-wife and her friend were 
savagely slaughtered, there was no outcry to ban long, serrated knives.  
</P>
<P>
 It is already a major crime to murder someone, whether by car, by gun or by 
knife. The law does not stop the crime. Gun bans do not work. Ask anyone in the 
nation's capital. You stated that you do not want more Spokane-style tragedies. 
Any responsible, law-abiding citizen does not want that either. 
</P>
<P>
 The kind of future we as responsible citizens see, is the kind of future where 
we don't need guns for defense against the bad guys, because the bad guys are 
gone. Gun owners are not the problem. 
</P>
<P>
 TIMOTHY SMITH 
</P>
<P>
 Pomona 
</P>
</TEXT>
