<HEADLINE>
<P>
CARSON; COUPLE CHOSEN TO HELP BUILD THEIR OWN HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The first South Bay family to get a home through the nonprofit group Habitat 
for Humanity will see construction of its house start this week. 
</P>
<P>
 The organization chose Gabriel and Maria Ceja of Carson from more than 100 
applicants. Through Habitat, the family will spend 500 hours working with 
volunteers to build the house and will take classes on home maintenance and 
budgeting. 
</P>
<P>
 The monthly payments they make will go into a general fund to help build more 
houses for needy people in Carson. 
</P>
<P>
 The groundbreaking ceremony is set for today at 11:30 a.m. 
</P>
