<TEXT>
<P>
 Patrick Ewing of the New York Knicks underwent a successful arthroscopy on his 
right knee to clean out loose cartilage. Ewing, who turns 32 on August 5, had 
similar procedures in 1986 and 1989. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 A federal investigation into the helicopter crash that killed NASCAR star 
Davey Allison points toward pilot inexperience on his part as a cause of the 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
 A 65-page report released by the National Transportation Safety Board said 
Allison had only 2.8 hours of flying instruction in his Hughes 369HS before the 
chopper went down last July 12 with him at the controls. The investigative 
report did not identify a specific cause of the accident. Hockey 
</P>
<P>
 The Philadelphia Flyers signed New York Ranger free-agent forward Craig 
MacTavish to a two-year contract worth about $1.6 million. 
</P>
