<P>
 FIFA reports it is satisfied with security arrangements during the World Cup. 
</P>
<P>
 There have been 312 arrests among the more than 2.5 million who have attended 
games. Of those arrests, 161 involved ticket scalping. Twelve have been 
arrested for public drunkenness. There also were 833 cases of fans requiring 
medical treatment, 95% for heat-related problems. ELLIOTT ALMOND 
