<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; SENT OFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELLIOTT ALMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What was supposed to be a joke ended in the deportation of Dutch journalist 
Lex Muller and his loss of a job. 
</P>
<P>
 Muller jokingly claimed Wednesday that there was a bomb on the chartered plane 
that was taking the Dutch national team from Orlando to Dallas, site of 
Saturday's Netherlands-Brazil quarterfinal game. The flight was delayed for 
about five hours as a bomb squad secured the area.  
</P>
<P>
 Airport officials held Muller in handcuffs before U.S. officials ordered his 
deportation, and his newspaper, Algeen Dagblad, fired him. ELLIOTT ALMOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
