<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOPICS; MEDICINE; HOSPITAL IN BALDWIN PARK CLOSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Baldwin Park hospital that was $750,000 in the red has closed its doors. 
</P>
<P>
 Terrace Plaza Medical Center on Francisquito Avenue had too little money even 
to finish the month of June, said Ernest Pooleon, supervisor of licensing at 
the county Department of Health Services.The for-profit hospital closed June 
22. 
</P>
<P>
 There were only a "smattering" of patients at the 95-bed hospital when it 
closed, Pooleon said. The patients were transferred to Queen of the Valley 
Hospital in West Covina and other local facilities, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The hospital filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy before the closure, but Pooleon 
did not know when. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The City of Hope National Medical Center has a toll-free hot line for 
questions on skin cancer prevention and other cancer-related topics, including 
early detection, diagnosis and treatment. 
</P>
<P>
 By calling CancerConnection, (800) 678-9990, people can talk to cancer nurses 
at the Duarte hospital about topics such as how to perform skin 
self-examinations, how to choose a sunscreen, and children's needs for skin and 
eye protection. 
</P>
