<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: BEVERLY HILLS; HAZARDOUS WASTE ROUNDUP SET FOR JULY 30 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A hazardous waste roundup for Westside residents will be held July 30 at the 
Beverly Hills Civic Center. 
</P>
<P>
 From 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. residents can dispose of such hazardous materials as 
paint, turpentine, pesticides, household and auto batteries and outdated 
prescription medicines. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is sponsored by Los Angeles County, in cooperation with Beverly 
Hills, Culver City, West Hollywood and Los Angeles. Organizers ask that no more 
than five gallons or 50 pounds of material be transported per vehicle. 
Containers should also be labeled, if possible. 
</P>
<P>
 The civic center is located at 9332 Civic Center Drive in Beverly Hills. For 
more information on hazardous waste prevention and disposal call (310) 
280-5950. 
</P>
