<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: WILSHIRE CENTER; STREETSCAPE PROJECT HOSTS BLOCK PARTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAKE DOHERTY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Wilshire Center Streetscape Project will sponsor a block party Saturday, 
the first major event in an effort to beautify the area. 
</P>
<P>
 The party will be along Mariposa Avenue between 7th and 8th streets from 8:30 
a.m. to 1 p.m. As part of the celebration, trees will be planted along Mariposa 
Avenue, the first phase of a project that will ultimately include planting 
2,500 trees throughout Wilshire Center.An event May 14 introduced residents to 
tree-planting techniques. 
</P>
<P>
 The $4.5-million project, with money from public and private sources, will 
also create crosswalks, new street lighting, bus stops and benches, artwork, a 
landscaped median along Wilshire Boulevard, and other physical and landscaping 
improvements. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents and people who work in Wilshire Center are invited to participate in 
the tree planting. Mariachis will provide entertainment, and local restaurants 
will offer free food. 
</P>
<P>
 The project is being coordinated by the Wilshire Chamber of Commerce, the 
Apartment Assn. of Greater Los Angeles, the Korean Youth and Community Center, 
and Portals House. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 393-5505 or (213) 383-1891. JAKE DOHERTY 
</P>
</TEXT>
