<P>
VENICE: LATINO VIEW OF GANG WAR SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I noticed that the article by Jeffrey Kramer on the Venice gang war contained 
no quotes from Latinos, who constitute 50% of the people in the Oakwood 
neighborhood.Twenty-five percent are black and 25% are white. The article 
implies, by its failure to quote from any Latinos, that this is a neighborhood 
with a black majority. 
</P>
<P>
 I am not a spokesperson for the Latino community. I have no idea what they 
think or feel, but I would like to know, and that is the job of the reporter. 
</P>
<P>
 Every story trots out that tired old conspiracy rumor that big developers have 
sponsored the gang war. Let's have more depth in the future. 
</P>
<P>
 MARY JEAN STEWART 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica  
