<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOTEBOOK / GARY KLEIN; WEST COVINA'S MOUNT, ARROYO'S MACKINNON SELECTED TO 
COACH ALL-STAR GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GARY KLEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The 15th annual Hall of Fame football all-star game, featuring recent high 
school graduates from the San Gabriel Valley, will be played July 15 at Citrus 
College. 
</P>
<P>
 The game, sponsored by the Pasadena/San Gabriel Valley chapter of the National 
Football Foundation and Hall of Fame, features players from as far west as 
Glendale to as far east as Chino. 
</P>
<P>
 Bob Mount of West Covina will coach the East team. Don MacKinnon of Arroyo 
will coach the West. 
</P>
<P>
 Sharon Lehman, who coached Linfield Christian in Temecula to two Southern 
Section softball championships, has been named softball coach at Azusa Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
 Lehman, who graduated from Azusa Pacific in 1982, succeeds Teri Corwin, who 
resigned after one season. 
</P>
<P>
 Roddy Layton, a wide receiver for the Mt. San Antonio College football team 
the past two seasons, was selected as a national scholar athlete by the 
National Alliance of Two-Year College Athletic Administrators. 
</P>
