<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; STUPID SOCCER TRICKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alexi Lalas' goatee got an impromptu trim, while the legend of Univision 
announcer Andres Cantor continues to grow. 
</P>
<P>
 Lalas and Cantor were both guests of David Letterman on the "Late Show" 
Wednesday night, and Letterman did some real cutting up. 
</P>
<P>
 Before doing what a lot of people would probably like to do, Letterman, near 
the end of an interview with Lalas, asked: "Can I trim that up for you, just a 
little, just a little, just take a little off? Even it off. That's all we're 
going to do." 
</P>
<P>
 Letterman trimmed about an inch off the goatee. 
</P>
<P>
 Lalas then kicked a soccer ball into the balcony of the Ed Sullivan Theater, 
causing Cantor to scream: "GOOOOOOAAAAAALLLL!!!!!" 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier, Lalas talked about how he was just a fan at the World Cup four years 
ago. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was in Italy, bumming around with high school friends, drinking beer, 
chasing women," Lalas said. 
</P>
<P>
 "You don't need a World Cup for that," Letterman interjected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
