<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; GREAT RATINGS IN ANY LANGUAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 KMEX (Channel 34), the Spanish-language station, scored a ratings victory 
Tuesday over all English-language L.A. stations from 1:30 to 4:30 p.m. with its 
coverage of the Mexico-Bulgaria game. 
</P>
<P>
 The game posted a 7.1 Nielsen rating and a 17 share, the best for KMEX in its 
33-year history, and reached 355,000 households. It peaked during the dramatic 
finish, when Bulgaria won on penalty kicks, getting an 8.5 rating and reaching 
425,000 households. 
</P>
<P>
 In Latino households, the game got a 43.7 rating and a 73 share, meaning it 
was seen in seven of 10 households where television was being watched. The 
Latino rating peaked at 48 during the final 15 minutes. LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</TEXT>
