<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; NOT QUITE BEGGING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Goalkeeper Borislav Mihaylov was happy for his compatriots that Bulgaria 
managed to beat Mexico Tuesday, but his motives weren't entirely altruistic. 
</P>
<P>
 By performing well in the tournament, he will attract attention from major 
European clubs. And he wasn't shy about letting them know he's available. 
</P>
<P>
 "I am looking forward to joining other teams with better offers," said 
Mihaylov, who plays for Mulhouse in the French Second Division. HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
