<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; BIG HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT WHITE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The 84,147 fans who filled Stanford Stadium on July 4 for the United 
States-Brazil game were more than 3,000 past the facility's listed World Cup 
capacity. 
</P>
<P>
 That attendance beat by 88 the crowd of 84,059 at Stanford for Super Bowl XIX 
in 1985, which matched the San Francisco 49ers and the Miami Dolphins. MATT 
WHITE 
</P>
