<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; FAST LEARNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dutch goalkeeper Ed de Goey is glad to see the attention soccer is getting in 
the United States, thanks to the World Cup. 
</P>
<P>
 "Now, the people are just starting to learn it, and maybe in a couple of years 
they will be more into it," he said. "Americans have to learn a lot about the 
sport. However, they seem really anxious to learn. The commentators on the game 
are growing (in knowledge) and doing much better than when we first came." 
HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
