<P>
AMERICAN LEGION BASEBALL; AMITIN AGAIN HITS WINNING TRIPLE AS VAN NUYS SOUTH 
BEATS SUN VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aaron Amitin tripled with two out in the sixth inning to drive in two runs and 
give Van Nuys South a 6-4 victory over Sun Valley in an American Legion 
District 20 game Wednesday at Grant High. 
</P>
<P>
 It marked the second game in a row Amitin has driven in the winning run with a 
triple. 
</P>
<P>
 Sun Valley (11-4) loaded the bases in the seventh before Mike Weiss struck out 
the last batter. 
</P>
<P>
 David Corleto homered for Van Nuys South (5-8). 
</P>
<P>
 In other District 20 games: 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills East 7, Granada Hills East 1 -- Rusty Jenkins (3-2) pitched a 
five-hitter, struck out two and walked four for Woodland Hills East (5-9) at 
Taft High. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Horowitz and David Helman each had two runs batted in. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys East 11, North Hollywood 1 -- Van Nuys East had 13 hits and Andy Lutz 
held North Hollywood to two hits at Notre Dame High. Van Nuys East (9-4) stole 
12 bases in as many attempts. Wes Clain and Joey Orlando each had three hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Canoga Park 8, Studio City 7 -- Sean Hansen hit a three-run home run in the 
sixth to lift Canoga Park at Faith Baptist High. Canoga Park rallied from a 6-0 
deficit. Alfredo Guerra had three hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Granada Hills West 2, West Hills 0 -- Jim O'Brien lined a two-run single in 
the fifth and three Granada Hills West pitchers combined on a one-hitter at 
Chaminade High. Adam Crecion singled for the only West Hills' hit. 
</P>
<P>
 Verdugo Hills 4, Sunland-Tujunga 3 -- Bryan Chan pitched a five-hitter, struck 
out 13 and walked three for Verdugo Hills (13-4). David Boger homered in the 
eighth for the winning run. 
</P>
