<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; PINYON PINES; FIREFIGHTERS EXPECT TO CONTAIN BLAZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fire crews had the end of a weeklong battle in sight, expecting that today 
they will encircle a mountain wildfire that destroyed 12 houses and five mobile 
homes south of Palm Springs. Authorities said they expected to have the 
19,600-acre blaze contained by tonight and virtually extinguished by Sunday 
night, said Karen McKinley, a U.S. Forest Service spokeswoman. Meanwhile, a 
10,000-acre fire 60 miles to the northwest in the San Bernardino National 
Forest was only 25% ringed by firebreaks Wednesday, but its movement northeast 
was slowing. 
</P>
