<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; STATE TO INSTALL GATE AT MCGRATH BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Prompted by an increase in crime at McGrath State Beach, park officials will 
install a gate at the entrance to the popular beach area between Oxnard and 
Ventura, officials announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting July 15, park rangers will close the new gate nightly at 10 p.m. and 
reopen every morning at 8 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Increased incidents of vandalism, theft, public disturbances and other crimes 
in recent months triggered the decision to install the gate, state park 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Although rangers and lifeguards respond to late-night emergencies at McGrath, 
they do not perform nightly patrols of the state beach, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Park officials said they hope the new gate will also keep motorists in 
four-wheel drive vehicles away from the sensitive wetlands along the mouth of 
the Santa Clara River. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
