</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As part of a once-a-year service, Harrison Industries will accept additional 
curbside trash from Ventura customers between Monday and July 15 at no 
additional cost, company officials announced. 
</P>
<P>
 On their regularly scheduled collection days, garbage trucks will pick up the 
equivalent of two extra 35-gallon barrels or bags, or the same amount of 
bundled brush. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura customers can also arrange disposal of large items, such as furniture 
or appliances, which will be picked up at half the normal cost, officials said. 
Arrangements must be made at least one day in advance. 
</P>
