<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; BUILDING AND SAFETY PROVIDER NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Camarillo city officials have selected a Torrance-based company to provide 
building and safety services for the city. 
</P>
<P>
 The firm, Charles Abbott Associates Inc., outbid several other agencies, 
including Ventura County, to win the contract to provide building and safety 
inspections, licenses and other services, City Manager Bill Little said. 
</P>
<P>
 The company received favorable recommendations from several other cities that 
use its services, Little said. "We anticipate that the users of our building 
and safety services will receive similar levels of competent and efficient 
assistance," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the 12-month contract, the company will receive no more than $420,000 of 
the fees it collects, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information on available services, residents should call 388-5395. 
J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
