<TEXT>
<P>
 Two gunmen walked into the paddock level at Hollywood Park racetrack in 
Inglewood on Tuesday, handcuffed two guards filling automated teller machines 
and made off with two bags containing a total of $300,000, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The robbers approached the armored car guards as they put money in the first 
of two machines about 6:40 a.m., took their guns, made them get down on the 
floor and handcuffed them, Inglewood Police Sgt. John Knapp said. 
</P>
<P>
 Access to the racetrack's upper level was not restricted at the time of the 
robbery because, at that time, employees are usually at work and trainers are 
exercising horses, Knapp said. 
