<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRL BURNED WHEN FIREWORKS IN HER PANTS POCKETS IGNITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 12-year-old girl suffered minor burns Wednesday when fireworks in her pants 
pockets ignited as she sat down on them in a movie theater lobby, fire 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Westminster girl, who was not identified because of her age, was treated 
at the scene for burns to the back of one leg and taken to a local hospital for 
brief observation before being released, Westminster Fire Capt. Robert Martin 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Apparently she sat down and somehow they ignited," Martin said. "They started 
a small fire in her pants and caused first- and second-degree burns, which are 
fairly minor." 
</P>
<P>
 The girl told firefighters she was carrying the fireworks in her rear pants 
pocket at a movie theater at the Westminster Mall. Just before 5 p.m., the 
fireworks, known as "poppers" went off as the girl sat down, Martin said. 
</P>
<P>
 Illegal in California, the fireworks contain a small amount of gunpowder and 
make a cracking sound when slapped against a hard surface. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl and her friends extinguished the fire by the time Martin arrived to 
treat her, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 "This doesn't happen every day," Martin said. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin said fire prevention investigators were looking into the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
