<P>
 U.S.-Japan Talks Unable to Reach Accord: The United States and Japan wrapped 
up trade talks in two of three areas without an agreement. Both sides were 
aiming to reach an agreement by the opening of the G-7 meeting of 
industrialized nations in Naples on Friday -- the first anniversary of this 
preliminary round of trade talks. The three areas -- opening up Japan's markets 
for insurance; for autos and auto parts, and getting the Japanese government to 
buy more American medical and telecommunications equipment -- are the heart of 
the framework talks. 
</P>
