Growth in Neighborhoods -- has given 12 California communities $4.7 million in 
special housing grants.The money will be used to assist first-time, low-income 
buyers with up to $20,000 in down payments.  
</P>
<P>
 Though none of the cities that have received grants are in Orange County, 
Wilson came here to announce the additional funding. Awards will be made in 
September. The state Department of Housing and Community Development sponsors 
the program. 
