<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; CAMBODIA; OFFICIAL, POLICE CHIEF HELD IN FAILED COUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A senior Cambodian official and the chief of police in charge of Phnom Penh 
were arrested in connection with a failed coup last weekend. Army 
reinforcements and armored personnel carriers were sent to patrol the city as 
fears of a second coup attempt swept the government. Officials, fearing 
assassination by leaders of the attempted coup still at large, stayed away from 
their offices and homes. 
</P>
