<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; RWANDA; TROOPS COULD STAY PAST JULY, FRANCE SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 France said that its creation of a haven for refugees in western Rwanda is a 
success but added that it might have to keep its troops there beyond a 
self-imposed July 31 deadline. France launched its operation in Rwanda with a 
view to turning over the mission to U.N. troops by the end of July. But only a 
very few countries have volunteered to contribute military units, and a lack of 
money and equipment has slowed their arrival. 
</P>
