<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: DOWNEY; HIGHER FEES SET FOR REDESIGNED GOLF COURSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Downey residents will be paying more to play on the Rio Hondo Golf Course when 
the municipal course reopens this fall after extensive renovation. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council last week approved fee increases to help pay for the 
$5-million redesign. 
</P>
<P>
 Fees for Downey residents will increase from $2 to $5, and fees for 
non-residents will go up from $16 to $25. The fee for senior citizens who play 
before 8 a.m. or after noon on weekdays increases from $9.50 to $13 for 
residents and $18 for non-residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
