<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Prop. 13 -- Sunday's editorial on the gubernatorial race mistakenly stated 
that Prop. 13 could be repealed by a two-thirds vote of the people. In fact, 
Prop. 13 could be repealed by a simple majority by either initiative or 
referendum. But a referendum first would require a two-thirds vote of both 
houses in the Legislature to be placed on the ballot. 
</P>
